# m5_chassis_distinctness.shot — M5 P10
#
# Spawns one of each chassis side-by-side. Verifies the per-chassis
# bone-length distinctness pass: Heavy is visibly the tallest + widest
# (torso 38 vs Trooper's 30, +27%), Scout is shortest and thinnest
# (-16% all over), Sniper has the long forearms + shins (tall lean
# stance), Engineer is the compact stocky build.
#
# Run:
#   ./soldut --shot tests/shots/m5_chassis_distinctness.shot
# Output:
#   build/shots/m5_chassis_distinctness/all_chassis.png
#
# Verification — eyeball the PNG and confirm:
#   - Heavy is visibly taller than Scout (~30% in stand height)
#   - Sniper's chest leans forward (head pose offset toward facing)
#   - Engineer's right arm doesn't aim at the cursor (tool pose)

window 1280 720
seed   7 7
out    build/shots/m5_chassis_distinctness

# Player chassis is Trooper (the reference silhouette). Loadout slot 1
# is the secondary, which the engineer-quirk gate uses to skip the
# right-arm aim drive — the player here is Trooper so that gate
# doesn't fire (active_slot == 0 by default).
loadout Trooper "Pulse Rifle" Sidearm Light Standard

# Player Trooper at the centerline of the row; camera smooth-follows
# to here. The clear floor patch is between the jet platform (tiles
# 12..22 in row 30 ≈ x=384..704) and the slope test bed (3 polys at
# x=1500..1987). 160 px spacing fits 5 chassis cleanly inside that
# window.
spawn_at 1060 984
mouse    640 360

# Y = 32*32 - 36 (feet_below_pelvis) - 4 (foot_clearance) = 984. The
# tutorial map's solid floor sits at row 32, so this puts every chassis
# pelvis above the same shared floor — gravity settles each one onto
# its own feet over the first few ticks.
extra_chassis Scout     740 984
extra_chassis Heavy     900 984
extra_chassis Sniper   1220 984
extra_chassis Engineer 1380 984

# Let the Verlet solver settle each chassis into its standing pose
# (post-physics anchor + slope check both run), then capture once.
at  90 shot all_chassis
at 120 end
